00:05:07.600 --> 00:05:11.280 align:middle line:84%
The most efficient
pump ever invented.

00:05:11.280 --> 00:05:12.680 align:middle line:90%
But the heart is more than that.

00:05:12.680 --> 00:05:15.290 align:middle line:90%


00:05:15.290 --> 00:05:17.370 align:middle line:10%
>>We did an experiment
here at HeartMath

00:05:17.370 --> 00:05:19.410 align:middle line:10%
to study how the
information flows

00:05:19.410 --> 00:05:21.570 align:middle line:10%
between the heart and the
brain, and we actually

00:05:21.570 --> 00:05:23.190 align:middle line:10%
discovered something
quite remarkable,

00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:24.690 align:middle line:10%
something that surprised us.

00:05:24.690 --> 00:05:40.850 align:middle line:90%


00:05:40.850 --> 00:05:42.500 align:middle line:84%
The participants
in the study were

00:05:42.500 --> 00:05:45.320 align:middle line:84%
connected to various sensors
to measure their brain waves,

00:05:45.320 --> 00:05:47.330 align:middle line:90%
their heartbeats, and so on.

00:05:47.330 --> 00:05:49.520 align:middle line:84%
And then they were
exposed to various images.

00:05:49.520 --> 00:05:52.640 align:middle line:84%
Some were high arousal,
like a car crash,

00:05:52.640 --> 00:05:54.170 align:middle line:84%
or a snake striking,
while others

00:05:54.170 --> 00:05:56.930 align:middle line:84%
were lower arousal images
like bunny rabbits and nature

00:05:56.930 --> 00:05:59.030 align:middle line:90%
scenes.

00:05:59.030 --> 00:06:02.180 align:middle line:84%
The participants were
asked to push a button.

00:06:02.180 --> 00:06:05.270 align:middle line:84%
They then saw a blank computer
screen for six seconds.

00:06:05.270 --> 00:06:07.160 align:middle line:84%
The computer then
randomly selected

00:06:07.160 --> 00:06:12.260 align:middle line:84%
one of these photographs that
it displayed for three seconds.

00:06:12.260 --> 00:06:15.060 align:middle line:84%
After that the screen
went blank for 10 seconds,

00:06:15.060 --> 00:06:17.060 align:middle line:84%
and they were prompted
to push the button again,

00:06:17.060 --> 00:06:20.060 align:middle line:84%
and they repeated this
protocol about 30 times.

00:06:20.060 --> 00:06:25.360 align:middle line:90%


00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:29.930 align:middle line:84%
When we analyzed all the data,
the results were astounding.

00:06:29.930 --> 00:06:32.320 align:middle line:84%
The heart seemed
to know the images

00:06:32.320 --> 00:06:37.555 align:middle line:84%
before the participants ever
saw the images with their eyes.

00:06:37.555 --> 00:06:40.660 align:middle line:84%
If the future picture was going
to be one of the emotionally

00:06:40.660 --> 00:06:42.850 align:middle line:84%
arousing ones, the
heart rate started

00:06:42.850 --> 00:06:47.020 align:middle line:84%
to drop about five seconds
before the image was randomly

00:06:47.020 --> 00:06:49.430 align:middle line:84%
selected to be
shown on the screen.

00:06:49.430 --> 00:06:52.140 align:middle line:84%
So nobody could know what this
future picture was going to be.

00:06:52.140 --> 00:06:56.860 align:middle line:90%


00:06:56.860 --> 00:07:00.550 align:middle line:84%
The heart had a much
greater de-acceleration

00:07:00.550 --> 00:07:03.367 align:middle line:84%
than if it was, say, going
to be a calm picture.

00:07:03.367 --> 00:07:07.940 align:middle line:90%


00:07:07.940 --> 00:07:09.770 align:middle line:84%
These results have
since been replicated

00:07:09.770 --> 00:07:12.860 align:middle line:84%
in many different independent
labs around the world,

00:07:12.860 --> 00:07:14.982 align:middle line:90%
actually.

00:07:14.982 --> 00:07:17.660 align:middle line:84%
Well, a lot of people say that
I don't feel it in my heart,

00:07:17.660 --> 00:07:18.800 align:middle line:90%
I feel it in my gut.

00:07:18.800 --> 00:07:20.840 align:middle line:84%
But here's what's
really happening.

00:07:20.840 --> 00:07:23.170 align:middle line:84%
The information comes
to the heart first.

00:07:23.170 --> 00:07:24.860 align:middle line:84%
The heart then sends
a different signal

00:07:24.860 --> 00:07:26.660 align:middle line:84%
to the brain which
we can measure.

00:07:26.660 --> 00:07:30.610 align:middle line:84%
Then you have a brain response,
and then a body response.

00:07:30.610 --> 00:07:32.780 align:middle line:84%
And with the body
response, like feeling

00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:35.220 align:middle line:84%
in the gut, or the hair
on the back of the neck,

00:07:35.220 --> 00:07:36.720 align:middle line:90%
is where it becomes conscious.

00:07:36.720 --> 00:07:41.060 align:middle line:84%
But the real flow of information
is heart, brain, body.

00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:43.100 align:middle line:84%
And this is all
happening in many seconds

00:07:43.100 --> 00:07:46.540 align:middle line:90%
before the actual event occurs.

00:07:46.540 --> 00:07:48.510 align:middle line:84%
So what this body of
research is telling

00:07:48.510 --> 00:07:51.150 align:middle line:84%
us is that the heart
seems to be connected

00:07:51.150 --> 00:07:54.300 align:middle line:84%
to a type of intuition that is
not bound by the limits of time

00:07:54.300 --> 00:07:55.740 align:middle line:90%
and space.

00:07:55.740 --> 00:07:57.390 align:middle line:84%
But what is that
