00:38:46.140 --> 00:38:47.430 align:middle line:90%
>>You're still sleeping?

00:38:47.430 --> 00:38:49.840 align:middle line:84%
>>He looked like he was
awake for many hours.

00:38:49.840 --> 00:38:51.900 align:middle line:90%
>>You don't know what happened?

00:38:51.900 --> 00:38:53.820 align:middle line:84%
>>I jumped out of
the bed, I never

00:38:53.820 --> 00:38:57.439 align:middle line:84%
did this before in front of
my brother, put on my clothes.

00:38:57.439 --> 00:38:58.516 align:middle line:90%
>>We will win!

00:38:58.516 --> 00:38:59.593 align:middle line:90%
We will win!

00:38:59.593 --> 00:39:00.670 align:middle line:90%
Find the cockroaches!

00:39:00.670 --> 00:39:01.750 align:middle line:90%
Find the cockroaches!

00:39:01.750 --> 00:39:02.830 align:middle line:90%
>> He said,

00:39:02.830 --> 00:39:06.440 align:middle line:84%
>>The president of our
country died last night.

00:39:06.440 --> 00:39:09.820 align:middle line:90%
>>They're going to kill us.

00:39:09.820 --> 00:39:11.570 align:middle line:90%
>>I come from a tribe of Tutsi.

00:39:11.570 --> 00:39:13.580 align:middle line:10%
It was well-loved.

00:39:13.580 --> 00:39:16.490 align:middle line:10%
And we kind of suspected
something might happen.

00:39:16.490 --> 00:39:18.830 align:middle line:84%
My parents sent me to
hide to a neighbor, who

00:39:18.830 --> 00:39:21.185 align:middle line:90%
was from the Hutu tribe.

00:39:21.185 --> 00:39:24.200 align:middle line:84%
It was a protestant
pastor, and he

00:39:24.200 --> 00:39:26.240 align:middle line:84%
put me to sleep in
a bathroom of three

00:39:26.240 --> 00:39:29.180 align:middle line:84%
by four feet with
other seven women.

00:39:29.180 --> 00:39:33.610 align:middle line:84%
We couldn't talk, we couldn't
speak, as the man told us,

00:39:33.610 --> 00:39:36.570 align:middle line:90%
>>I won't even tell my children.

00:39:36.570 --> 00:39:38.090 align:middle line:90%
One mistake, one mistake.

00:39:38.090 --> 00:39:39.756 align:middle line:84%
It's not that I don't
trust my children,

00:39:39.756 --> 00:39:42.460 align:middle line:84%
but this mistake, it
would be too late for you

00:39:42.460 --> 00:39:46.188 align:middle line:90%
and your life will be over.

00:39:46.188 --> 00:39:49.820 align:middle line:90%
Don't use the shower.

00:39:49.820 --> 00:39:52.067 align:middle line:84%
>>Only flush the
water of the bathroom

00:39:52.067 --> 00:39:54.400 align:middle line:84%
when someone is flushing the
water in the next bathroom.

00:39:54.400 --> 00:39:58.204 align:middle line:90%


00:39:58.204 --> 00:39:59.787 align:middle line:84%
>>I think
[? that we'll be in for ?] a

00:39:59.787 --> 00:40:01.540 align:middle line:90%
week or maybe less.

00:40:01.540 --> 00:40:05.160 align:middle line:84%
But if we are careful, we
might live through this.

00:40:05.160 --> 00:40:06.580 align:middle line:90%
Just be careful.

00:40:06.580 --> 00:40:09.660 align:middle line:90%


00:40:09.660 --> 00:40:12.840 align:middle line:84%
>>We thought it was going
to be two, three days.

00:40:12.840 --> 00:40:17.385 align:middle line:84%
We spent in that
bathroom three months.

00:40:17.385 --> 00:40:20.342 align:middle line:84%
>>You must not let
your guard down.

00:40:20.342 --> 00:40:22.050 align:middle line:84%
The Tutsi snakes are
hiding in the grass,

00:40:22.050 --> 00:40:25.056 align:middle line:84%
so make sure that you have
your [INAUDIBLE] ready to chop

00:40:25.056 --> 00:40:26.110 align:middle line:90%
the snakes in half.

00:40:26.110 --> 00:40:27.410 align:middle line:90%
>>We couldn't shower.

00:40:27.410 --> 00:40:31.730 align:middle line:84%
We were waiting for killers
to find us every day.

00:40:31.730 --> 00:40:33.920 align:middle line:84%
>>If you're working
a field and spot

00:40:33.920 --> 00:40:36.670 align:middle line:84%
a Tutsi woman in the bushes
breastfeeding her baby,

00:40:36.670 --> 00:40:39.006 align:middle line:84%
don't waste a
golden opportunity.

00:40:39.006 --> 00:40:42.340 align:middle line:84%
Pick up your gun, shoot them,
chop the snakes in half.

00:40:42.340 --> 00:40:44.300 align:middle line:90%
Don't forget to kill the baby.

00:40:44.300 --> 00:40:47.280 align:middle line:90%
The child of a snake is a snake.

00:40:47.280 --> 00:40:49.740 align:middle line:84%
>>They went home
by home to search,

00:40:49.740 --> 00:40:51.570 align:middle line:90%
to see if anyone was hiding.

00:40:51.570 --> 00:40:54.900 align:middle line:84%
And this was a group that was
paid by the government, given

00:40:54.900 --> 00:40:57.240 align:middle line:90%
food, and drink, smokes.

00:40:57.240 --> 00:41:00.230 align:middle line:84%
The first time they came,
I remember I was watching,

00:41:00.230 --> 00:41:02.864 align:middle line:84%
and I saw them through the
tiny window of the bathroom.

00:41:02.864 --> 00:41:07.540 align:middle line:90%


00:41:07.540 --> 00:41:10.732 align:middle line:84%
The men circled the house
so that no one jumps out

00:41:10.732 --> 00:41:12.690 align:middle line:84%
of the window, and then
they started to scream.

00:41:12.690 --> 00:41:17.100 align:middle line:90%


00:41:17.100 --> 00:41:22.590 align:middle line:84%
They went in every room,
they went under the beds,

00:41:22.590 --> 00:41:25.975 align:middle line:84%
they even opened suitcases to
make sure there was no babies

00:41:25.975 --> 00:41:26.775 align:middle line:90%
hiding.

00:41:26.775 --> 00:41:30.540 align:middle line:90%


00:41:30.540 --> 00:41:32.250 align:middle line:84%
They went in the
ceiling of the house

00:41:32.250 --> 00:41:36.214 align:middle line:84%
with flashlights to make sure
no one is hiding in the ceiling.

00:41:36.214 --> 00:41:37.630 align:middle line:84%
They went on the
roof of the house

00:41:37.630 --> 00:41:40.690 align:middle line:84%
to make sure no one
is laying there.

00:41:40.690 --> 00:41:45.170 align:middle line:84%
I remember asking, if you are
there, can control all this,

00:41:45.170 --> 00:41:50.535 align:middle line:84%
please don't let them find
the door of the bathroom.

00:41:50.535 --> 00:41:53.240 align:middle line:84%
A thousand needles
went through your body.

00:41:53.240 --> 00:41:54.500 align:middle line:90%
It was painful.

00:41:54.500 --> 00:41:56.860 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't a little
fear, it was a lot.

00:41:56.860 --> 00:41:58.480 align:middle line:90%
Your life was about to be over.

00:41:58.480 --> 00:42:00.310 align:middle line:84%
You are about to
be cut by machetes.

00:42:00.310 --> 00:42:04.430 align:middle line:90%


00:42:04.430 --> 00:42:05.555 align:middle line:90%
>>Where are the Tutsis?

00:42:05.555 --> 00:42:07.680 align:middle line:84%
>>No, no, no, don't know
what you're talking about.

00:42:07.680 --> 00:42:08.640 align:middle line:90%
I'm a good Hutu.

00:42:08.640 --> 00:42:10.910 align:middle line:84%
I would never hide Tutsis,
there are no Tutsis here.

00:42:10.910 --> 00:42:14.845 align:middle line:84%
I don't want any problem
with the government.

00:42:14.845 --> 00:42:16.994 align:middle line:84%
You know me, I shall
protect this house.

00:42:16.994 --> 00:42:18.910 align:middle line:84%
First those Tutsi rebels
come in and attack me

00:42:18.910 --> 00:42:20.940 align:middle line:90%
for being such a good Hutu.

00:42:20.940 --> 00:42:23.269 align:middle line:84%
>>They came right to the
door of the bathroom.

00:42:23.269 --> 00:42:24.560 align:middle line:90%
One of them touched the handle.

00:42:24.560 --> 00:42:29.741 align:middle line:90%


00:42:29.741 --> 00:42:31.520 align:middle line:90%
He told the man,

00:42:31.520 --> 00:42:32.320 align:middle line:90%
>>You know what?

00:42:32.320 --> 00:42:35.300 align:middle line:90%


00:42:35.300 --> 00:42:38.060 align:middle line:90%
I trust you.

00:42:38.060 --> 00:42:39.532 align:middle line:90%
You are a good man.

00:42:39.532 --> 00:42:40.576 align:middle line:90%
>>Oh, thank you.

00:42:40.576 --> 00:42:44.050 align:middle line:90%


00:42:44.050 --> 00:42:45.658 align:middle line:90%
>>You are one of us now.

00:42:45.658 --> 00:42:50.110 align:middle line:90%


00:42:50.110 --> 00:42:51.852 align:middle line:84%
>>I mean, when we
saw him, we jumped.

00:42:51.852 --> 00:42:53.560 align:middle line:84%
We thought it was the
killers finding us.

00:42:53.560 --> 00:42:54.900 align:middle line:90%
>>You're safe now.

00:42:54.900 --> 00:42:56.540 align:middle line:90%
You're lucky to be alive.

00:42:56.540 --> 00:43:01.160 align:middle line:84%
>>We were completely numb
for the first five hours.

00:43:01.160 --> 00:43:02.980 align:middle line:84%
>>I don't know how
you are praying,

00:43:02.980 --> 00:43:04.150 align:middle line:90%
or if you're even praying.

00:43:04.150 --> 00:43:07.182 align:middle line:84%
But whatever you're doing,
please keep doing it.

00:43:07.182 --> 00:43:11.630 align:middle line:90%


00:43:11.630 --> 00:43:15.010 align:middle line:84%
>>You know, the feelings
I had in that bathroom

00:43:15.010 --> 00:43:19.610 align:middle line:84%
were things I never
experienced in my life.

00:43:19.610 --> 00:43:22.970 align:middle line:84%
I had anger, anger I
cannot put in words.

00:43:22.970 --> 00:43:26.180 align:middle line:84%
I mean, sometimes
people hate one person,

00:43:26.180 --> 00:43:27.560 align:middle line:90%
and that's bad enough.

00:43:27.560 --> 00:43:29.990 align:middle line:84%
I hated like eight
million people.

00:43:29.990 --> 00:43:32.590 align:middle line:84%
And I remember thinking,
when I got out,

00:43:32.590 --> 00:43:34.310 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to be a
soldier, and I will

00:43:34.310 --> 00:43:38.050 align:middle line:84%
train my body, and muscles,
and just kill everybody.

00:43:38.050 --> 00:43:41.480 align:middle line:90%
In my anger, I was Rambo.

00:43:41.480 --> 00:43:45.740 align:middle line:84%
In some movies I have
seen, I was killing people.

00:43:45.740 --> 00:43:49.030 align:middle line:84%
With these thoughts I would
be swearing out of anger.

00:43:49.030 --> 00:43:52.880 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting in the
bathroom with these thoughts,

00:43:52.880 --> 00:43:57.680 align:middle line:84%
my head would be aching,
and my stomach is aching.

00:43:57.680 --> 00:44:00.840 align:middle line:84%
Why my thoughts are
provoking this poison?

00:44:00.840 --> 00:44:03.810 align:middle line:84%
I'm only thinking of
things I want to do.

00:44:03.810 --> 00:44:05.820 align:middle line:84%
What is going on with
my thoughts here?

00:44:05.820 --> 00:44:08.500 align:middle line:90%


00:44:08.500 --> 00:44:12.520 align:middle line:84%
>>It's very hard to remember
love when we are scared.

00:44:12.520 --> 00:44:14.620 align:middle line:84%
Being afraid is one
of the strongest

00:44:14.620 --> 00:44:17.080 align:middle line:90%
emotions in the world.

00:44:17.080 --> 00:44:19.880 align:middle line:84%
>>Our heart rate varies with
each and every heartbeat.

00:44:19.880 --> 00:44:23.710 align:middle line:84%
And when we're frustrated, and
anxious, and emotionally upset,

00:44:23.710 --> 00:44:26.840 align:middle line:84%
the rhythm of the heart becomes
very incoherent and jagged.

00:44:26.840 --> 00:44:29.080 align:middle line:84%
And this basically
creates a noise

00:44:29.080 --> 00:44:32.300 align:middle line:84%
in the system that drowns
out the intuitive signals.

00:44:32.300 --> 00:44:36.910 align:middle line:84%
>>I remember thinking, this
home has two bathrooms.

00:44:36.910 --> 00:44:38.980 align:middle line:84%
If they didn't have
these two bathrooms,

00:44:38.980 --> 00:44:41.520 align:middle line:84%
how could we have
been hidden here?

00:44:41.520 --> 00:44:42.910 align:middle line:90%
They would have find us.

00:44:42.910 --> 00:44:46.360 align:middle line:84%
It was only home that had two
bathrooms inside the house,

00:44:46.360 --> 00:44:49.780 align:middle line:90%
and that made me feel good.

00:44:49.780 --> 00:44:53.470 align:middle line:84%
When I was thinking the
good, it was so distinctive

00:44:53.470 --> 00:44:55.810 align:middle line:84%
because the feelings
were so high you

00:44:55.810 --> 00:44:59.080 align:middle line:84%
can feel the difference
like someone just pushed you

00:44:59.080 --> 00:45:01.180 align:middle line:90%
down and lifted you up.

00:45:01.180 --> 00:45:03.400 align:middle line:90%
Like it's so clearly.

00:45:03.400 --> 00:45:06.355 align:middle line:84%
And I started
thinking, we can eat.

00:45:06.355 --> 00:45:08.240 align:middle line:90%
Thank God this man has children.

00:45:08.240 --> 00:45:11.590 align:middle line:84%
We can eat the leftovers,
even if it was not much.

00:45:11.590 --> 00:45:14.140 align:middle line:84%
So I started to see
the good, and it

00:45:14.140 --> 00:45:16.430 align:middle line:90%
was like my heart was open.

00:45:16.430 --> 00:45:19.650 align:middle line:84%
Look at these people,
I can touch somebody.

00:45:19.650 --> 00:45:22.390 align:middle line:84%
Just to see the
good in everything.

00:45:22.390 --> 00:45:25.710 align:middle line:84%
>>Appreciation is a
heart related feeling.

00:45:25.710 --> 00:45:27.640 align:middle line:84%
It requires access
to the intelligence

00:45:27.640 --> 00:45:31.250 align:middle line:84%
of the heart to appreciate,
or to have gratitude.

00:45:31.250 --> 00:45:35.670 align:middle line:84%
>>And when I was thinking
that way, I felt much smarter.

00:45:35.670 --> 00:45:37.590 align:middle line:84%
>>When we're in
a coherent state,

00:45:37.590 --> 00:45:40.090 align:middle line:84%
the signal from the heart to
the brain is so much stronger.

00:45:40.090 --> 00:45:43.320 align:middle line:84%
It gets up to our frontal
cortex much clearer.

00:45:43.320 --> 00:45:45.310 align:middle line:84%
>>That's the heart
knocking on your door,

00:45:45.310 --> 00:45:47.590 align:middle line:84%
saying, open the
door, here I am.

00:45:47.590 --> 00:45:49.750 align:middle line:90%
You need me.

00:45:49.750 --> 00:45:52.310 align:middle line:84%
Because then you
say, ooh, where am I?

00:45:52.310 --> 00:45:55.016 align:middle line:90%
I'm in hell.

00:45:55.016 --> 00:45:57.620 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know that.

00:45:57.620 --> 00:46:01.525 align:middle line:84%
But the heart tells
you, trust me.

00:46:01.525 --> 00:46:03.420 align:middle line:90%
And when you're out of that--

00:46:03.420 --> 00:46:06.430 align:middle line:84%
>>It begins to shift the
energies very, very quickly

00:46:06.430 --> 00:46:09.560 align:middle line:84%
so that you come into another
level of buoyancy that

00:46:09.560 --> 00:46:11.530 align:middle line:90%
rises above the problem.

00:46:11.530 --> 00:46:14.030 align:middle line:84%
And in doing so, you
can then see into it.

00:46:14.030 --> 00:46:18.580 align:middle line:84%
You can then find
ways to deal with it.

00:46:18.580 --> 00:46:21.010 align:middle line:90%
>>They're coming back.

00:46:21.010 --> 00:46:23.410 align:middle line:90%
>>It was so clear in my heart.

00:46:23.410 --> 00:46:25.791 align:middle line:90%
This time they want to find you.

00:46:25.791 --> 00:46:28.146 align:middle line:90%
>>Pastor.

00:46:28.146 --> 00:46:30.480 align:middle line:84%
Push the wardrobe in
front of the door.

00:46:30.480 --> 00:46:32.443 align:middle line:84%
They're not going to
see there is a door.

00:46:32.443 --> 00:46:33.832 align:middle line:90%
>>No, no, why?

00:46:33.832 --> 00:46:36.123 align:middle line:84%
If they come, they'll
realize it wasn't here.

00:46:36.123 --> 00:46:37.485 align:middle line:90%
>>I'm begging you.

00:46:37.485 --> 00:46:42.930 align:middle line:90%


00:46:42.930 --> 00:46:44.415 align:middle line:90%
>>OK.

00:46:44.415 --> 00:46:48.880 align:middle line:90%
OK, OK, I will put it.

00:46:48.880 --> 00:46:52.710 align:middle line:84%
>>And it was so clear that
I need to listen to that.

00:46:52.710 --> 00:47:05.710 align:middle line:90%


00:47:05.710 --> 00:47:06.795 align:middle line:90%
They came to search.

00:47:06.795 --> 00:47:14.325 align:middle line:90%


00:47:14.325 --> 00:47:15.774 align:middle line:90%
>>Where is she, Pastor?

00:47:15.774 --> 00:47:17.926 align:middle line:84%
This is the last
place she was seen.

00:47:17.926 --> 00:47:19.372 align:middle line:90%
We know she's here.

00:47:19.372 --> 00:47:22.264 align:middle line:90%


00:47:22.264 --> 00:47:23.228 align:middle line:90%
Immaculee!

00:47:23.228 --> 00:47:26.130 align:middle line:90%


00:47:26.130 --> 00:47:32.790 align:middle line:84%
>>One of them said, I've
killed 399 cockroaches.

00:47:32.790 --> 00:47:36.876 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I want
Immaculee to be the 400th.

00:47:36.876 --> 00:47:38.920 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking,
this man, I knew him.

00:47:38.920 --> 00:47:41.920 align:middle line:84%
He was a school mate
in elementary school.

00:47:41.920 --> 00:47:43.910 align:middle line:90%
Someone I can call a friend.

00:47:43.910 --> 00:47:48.916 align:middle line:84%
How can somebody say he
killed 399 people by machete,

00:47:48.916 --> 00:47:51.380 align:middle line:90%
but he was proud?

00:47:51.380 --> 00:47:53.516 align:middle line:90%
They went right in the wardrobe.

00:47:53.516 --> 00:48:00.656 align:middle line:90%


00:48:00.656 --> 00:48:04.970 align:middle line:84%
They could have find us if
that wardrobe was not there.

00:48:04.970 --> 00:48:08.120 align:middle line:90%
And later he said, good idea.

00:48:08.120 --> 00:48:10.700 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't even like I wanted
to take credit, like oh good,

00:48:10.700 --> 00:48:12.110 align:middle line:90%
I had a good idea.

00:48:12.110 --> 00:48:15.380 align:middle line:84%
It was just like,
keep listening.

00:48:15.380 --> 00:48:21.260 align:middle line:84%
Know how to distinguish that
clarity that is not covered by

00:48:21.260 --> 00:48:25.500 align:middle line:84%
hate, by envy, by jealousy,
by anything unloving.

00:48:25.500 --> 00:48:27.350 align:middle line:90%
That is really how it comes out.

00:48:27.350 --> 00:48:30.500 align:middle line:84%
It comes as a
truth that you know

00:48:30.500 --> 00:48:36.650 align:middle line:84%
is not motivated by
something not nice.

00:48:36.650 --> 00:48:38.880 align:middle line:84%
And the funny part,
when they left,

00:48:38.880 --> 00:48:40.760 align:middle line:90%
the anger came right back.

00:48:40.760 --> 00:48:43.190 align:middle line:84%
It was just like a
[INAUDIBLE] oil coming back

00:48:43.190 --> 00:48:47.510 align:middle line:84%
on the top of the water, like
a veil I pulled in front.

00:48:47.510 --> 00:48:49.400 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't say,
I couldn't think.

00:48:49.400 --> 00:48:53.180 align:middle line:84%
Oh, my body's aching
again, and my headache.

00:48:53.180 --> 00:48:56.660 align:middle line:84%
But that's what you do when
people are killing your people.

00:48:56.660 --> 00:48:57.950 align:middle line:90%
You get angry.

00:48:57.950 --> 00:49:04.090 align:middle line:84%
So I didn't even think there was
another way to deal with this.

00:49:04.090 --> 00:49:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Despite the price I was
paying with my own body,

00:49:08.450 --> 00:49:11.330 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't remember how
to smile cause of anger.

00:49:11.330 --> 00:49:13.880 align:middle line:84%
I felt like my
mouth was twisted.

00:49:13.880 --> 00:49:16.280 align:middle line:90%
I wished to be innocent again.

00:49:16.280 --> 00:49:18.360 align:middle line:90%
I wished to see good in people.

00:49:18.360 --> 00:49:20.660 align:middle line:90%
But for me, they were animals.

00:49:20.660 --> 00:49:22.190 align:middle line:90%
They were bad.

00:49:22.190 --> 00:49:25.460 align:middle line:90%
They were just evil people.

00:49:25.460 --> 00:49:29.850 align:middle line:84%
Every day I prayed about
200 our Lord's Prayer.

00:49:29.850 --> 00:49:33.950 align:middle line:90%


00:49:33.950 --> 00:49:40.760 align:middle line:84%
Any time I reached the part that
said, forgive us our trespasses

00:49:40.760 --> 00:49:46.339 align:middle line:84%
as we forgive those who trespass
against us, I couldn't say it.

00:49:46.339 --> 00:49:49.032 align:middle line:84%
>>Give us this day
our daily bread.

00:49:49.032 --> 00:49:49.832 align:middle line:90%
Forgive--

00:49:49.832 --> 00:49:53.830 align:middle line:90%


00:49:53.830 --> 00:49:57.560 align:middle line:84%
>>Any time I went through that
part it was like a red flag.

00:49:57.560 --> 00:49:59.790 align:middle line:84%
And then I said, how
can I deal with it?

00:49:59.790 --> 00:50:05.660 align:middle line:84%
Because I can't forgive, because
this is unforgivable thing.

00:50:05.660 --> 00:50:06.920 align:middle line:90%
They tried to kill me.

00:50:06.920 --> 00:50:08.720 align:middle line:90%
How do you forgive such a thing?

00:50:08.720 --> 00:50:12.590 align:middle line:84%
I wished I could, but it didn't
make sense in my situation.

00:50:12.590 --> 00:50:16.130 align:middle line:84%
So one time I said, wait a
minute, I have a better idea.

00:50:16.130 --> 00:50:19.350 align:middle line:84%
I thought, let me skip
that part of the prayer.

00:50:19.350 --> 00:50:22.550 align:middle line:84%
So then I don't have to say
it, then I can say the rest.

00:50:22.550 --> 00:50:27.140 align:middle line:84%
So then within me, God is OK,
now he knows I'm not lying.

00:50:27.140 --> 00:50:29.300 align:middle line:90%
Lies don't sit well in the body.

00:50:29.300 --> 00:50:34.620 align:middle line:84%
And I start to skip it,
and I felt so much better.

00:50:34.620 --> 00:50:37.220 align:middle line:84%
So I edited it, and
now this voice says--

00:50:37.220 --> 00:50:39.770 align:middle line:90%
>>You are editing his prayer.

00:50:39.770 --> 00:50:43.920 align:middle line:84%
>>If I were you, I wouldn't
try to edit his prayer.

00:50:43.920 --> 00:50:45.740 align:middle line:84%
You know, I can say
this laughing today,

00:50:45.740 --> 00:50:48.960 align:middle line:84%
but that time my
mood was crushed.

00:50:48.960 --> 00:50:55.010 align:middle line:84%
I remember it was like giving
up, or can I call it surrender?

00:50:55.010 --> 00:51:00.260 align:middle line:84%
I went to my knees, and I put
my hands up, and I begged God.

00:51:00.260 --> 00:51:02.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to put
it back in prayer.

00:51:02.120 --> 00:51:05.210 align:middle line:84%
Because if you said pray
this way, you must know

00:51:05.210 --> 00:51:06.860 align:middle line:90%
it is the right thing to do.

00:51:06.860 --> 00:51:08.600 align:middle line:90%
I'm putting it in your hands.

00:51:08.600 --> 00:51:10.910 align:middle line:84%
If you know how to
forgive, help me out.

00:51:10.910 --> 00:51:12.260 align:middle line:90%
I am willing.

00:51:12.260 --> 00:51:13.300 align:middle line:90%
That was a big shift.

00:51:13.300 --> 00:51:32.370 align:middle line:90%


00:51:32.370 --> 00:51:36.170 align:middle line:84%
I remember they came to a point
when it was like the world was

00:51:36.170 --> 00:51:37.874 align:middle line:90%
divided in two parts.

00:51:37.874 --> 00:51:41.260 align:middle line:84%
A part of love,
and a part of hate.

00:51:41.260 --> 00:51:44.250 align:middle line:84%
In the part of love are
people like Mandela,

00:51:44.250 --> 00:51:46.940 align:middle line:90%
like Mother Teresa, Gandhi.

00:51:46.940 --> 00:51:47.930 align:middle line:90%
People who suffered.

00:51:47.930 --> 00:51:50.200 align:middle line:84%
And no matter how
much they suffered,

00:51:50.200 --> 00:51:52.570 align:middle line:90%
they still stand up for truth.

00:51:52.570 --> 00:51:55.300 align:middle line:84%
They still stand up
for love, for defense

00:51:55.300 --> 00:51:57.640 align:middle line:90%
of another human being's rights.

00:51:57.640 --> 00:52:01.210 align:middle line:84%
And then on the side of hate,
I see people like Hitler,

00:52:01.210 --> 00:52:04.200 align:middle line:84%
like those who were causing
genocide in Rwanda who

00:52:04.200 --> 00:52:08.020 align:middle line:84%
are vengeful, angry,
like me at that time.

00:52:08.020 --> 00:52:11.830 align:middle line:84%
And I felt like God was asking
me, where do you want to stand?

00:52:11.830 --> 00:52:13.364 align:middle line:90%
Where do you want to belong?

00:52:13.364 --> 00:52:17.346 align:middle line:90%


00:52:17.346 --> 00:52:21.205 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to belong to side
of love or the side of hate?

00:52:21.205 --> 00:52:22.450 align:middle line:90%
And guess what?

00:52:22.450 --> 00:52:24.310 align:middle line:84%
People who belong
on the side of love,

00:52:24.310 --> 00:52:26.930 align:middle line:90%
they have known injustice.

00:52:26.930 --> 00:52:28.970 align:middle line:90%
They have known hate.

00:52:28.970 --> 00:52:31.180 align:middle line:84%
They have known how
to be treated bad.

00:52:31.180 --> 00:52:32.286 align:middle line:90%
But it's your choice.

00:52:32.286 --> 00:52:36.892 align:middle line:90%


00:52:36.892 --> 00:52:40.430 align:middle line:84%
And I remember, it was
so clear that I said,

00:52:40.430 --> 00:52:43.000 align:middle line:84%
of course I want to be
with Gandhi, with Mandela.

00:52:43.000 --> 00:52:44.560 align:middle line:90%
I admire these people.

00:52:44.560 --> 00:52:46.690 align:middle line:90%
I admired Mother Teresa.

00:52:46.690 --> 00:52:47.930 align:middle line:90%
I want to be like them.

00:52:47.930 --> 00:52:49.090 align:middle line:90%
So what did they do?

00:52:49.090 --> 00:52:51.490 align:middle line:90%
They believed people can change.

00:52:51.490 --> 00:52:57.010 align:middle line:84%
That was a huge shift in
my thinking in my body.

00:52:57.010 --> 00:52:58.840 align:middle line:90%
People do change.

00:52:58.840 --> 00:53:00.820 align:middle line:84%
And I remember
thinking, wait a minute.

00:53:00.820 --> 00:53:03.220 align:middle line:84%
I don't think people
can really change.

00:53:03.220 --> 00:53:05.500 align:middle line:90%
Now, wait a minute again.

00:53:05.500 --> 00:53:07.980 align:middle line:84%
Look at me, I'm changing
with all these thoughts.

00:53:07.980 --> 00:53:11.380 align:middle line:90%


00:53:11.380 --> 00:53:15.140 align:middle line:84%
So when I realized that
people actually do change,

00:53:15.140 --> 00:53:19.390 align:middle line:84%
people have the capacity
to see things differently,

00:53:19.390 --> 00:53:22.450 align:middle line:84%
that's when I realized
I can let it go.

00:53:22.450 --> 00:53:27.100 align:middle line:84%
I felt like I moved from the
bathroom to a place of air.

00:53:27.100 --> 00:53:30.440 align:middle line:90%
That's how love felt in my body.

00:53:30.440 --> 00:53:32.000 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't smell nothing bad.

00:53:32.000 --> 00:53:34.000 align:middle line:90%
It was like I was floating.

00:53:34.000 --> 00:53:37.000 align:middle line:90%


00:53:37.000 --> 00:53:40.872 align:middle line:84%
And that was a
paradise in my heart.

00:53:40.872 --> 00:53:43.800 align:middle line:84%
I thought about the
killers, I should

00:53:43.800 --> 00:53:47.740 align:middle line:90%
have compassion towards them.

00:53:47.740 --> 00:53:52.150 align:middle line:84%
Imagine the person who
killed 100 people, who

00:53:52.150 --> 00:53:55.370 align:middle line:84%
have took away fathers and
mothers from their kids.

00:53:55.370 --> 00:53:59.420 align:middle line:84%
What are they going to become
when they wake up one day

00:53:59.420 --> 00:54:01.180 align:middle line:84%
and they realize
what they're doing?

00:54:01.180 --> 00:54:02.750 align:middle line:84%
Someone who begged
them for life?

00:54:02.750 --> 00:54:14.490 align:middle line:90%


00:54:14.490 --> 00:54:17.850 align:middle line:84%
When we came out, it was
like end of the world.

00:54:17.850 --> 00:54:20.444 align:middle line:84%
A million people
and more was killed.

00:54:20.444 --> 00:54:26.930 align:middle line:84%
My mom, my father, my
two brothers, my grandma

00:54:26.930 --> 00:54:29.750 align:middle line:90%
and my grandpa, neighbors.

00:54:29.750 --> 00:54:32.690 align:middle line:90%
My schoolmates, my best friends.

00:54:32.690 --> 00:54:34.920 align:middle line:90%
It was the end of the world.

00:54:34.920 --> 00:54:37.240 align:middle line:90%
Everywhere was their bodies.

00:54:37.240 --> 00:54:39.800 align:middle line:84%
But something have
changed in my heart.

00:54:39.800 --> 00:54:41.330 align:middle line:90%
I was strong inside.

00:54:41.330 --> 00:54:45.200 align:middle line:84%
I was really ready to face
life in a different way.

00:54:45.200 --> 00:54:46.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm a skeleton.

00:54:46.820 --> 00:54:48.580 align:middle line:90%
I'm 65 pounds.

00:54:48.580 --> 00:54:53.030 align:middle line:84%
But inside, I felt huge,
I felt more beautiful.

00:54:53.030 --> 00:54:55.670 align:middle line:84%
I felt like everybody
was just a gift of God,

00:54:55.670 --> 00:54:59.840 align:middle line:84%
and I just wanted to serve,
to help, and to care.

00:54:59.840 --> 00:55:02.480 align:middle line:84%
For the first time
I'm being grateful

00:55:02.480 --> 00:55:06.080 align:middle line:84%
for things I took
for granted forever.

00:55:06.080 --> 00:55:09.560 align:middle line:84%
And I can say hi to somebody
without anyone killing me.

00:55:09.560 --> 00:55:13.300 align:middle line:84%
And then I remember in
evening, this nice wind.

00:55:13.300 --> 00:55:17.180 align:middle line:84%
The trees are moving, I can
feel the wind in my body.

00:55:17.180 --> 00:55:19.580 align:middle line:84%
I didn't feel this
for three months.

00:55:19.580 --> 00:55:22.470 align:middle line:84%
I can see the stars,
I can see the moon,

00:55:22.470 --> 00:55:23.853 align:middle line:84%
and I don't have
to pay for this.

00:55:23.853 --> 00:55:26.620 align:middle line:84%
Did I ever looked at
the moon and said,

00:55:26.620 --> 00:55:28.310 align:middle line:90%
wow, nice to have the moon?

00:55:28.310 --> 00:55:29.540 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:55:29.540 --> 00:55:33.380 align:middle line:84%
It was overwhelming feeling
of love and appreciation.

00:55:33.380 --> 00:55:36.380 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to scream
to the whole world.

00:55:36.380 --> 00:55:39.775 align:middle line:90%
Do you see the beauty?

00:55:39.775 --> 00:55:47.810 align:middle line:84%
>>The mind can understand
conceptually wholeness,

00:55:47.810 --> 00:55:50.490 align:middle line:84%
but only the hard can
experience wholeness.

00:55:50.490 --> 00:55:53.780 align:middle line:90%


00:55:53.780 --> 00:55:56.980 align:middle line:84%
And the reward, if we can
endure what we experience,

00:55:56.980 --> 00:56:01.620 align:middle line:84%
is that we don't just
grasp oneness, we feel it.

00:56:01.620 --> 00:56:04.790 align:middle line:90%


00:56:04.790 --> 00:56:13.340 align:middle line:84%
>>Your head sees things
as black or white, wrong

00:56:13.340 --> 00:56:19.290 align:middle line:90%
or right, bad or good.

00:56:19.290 --> 00:56:24.310 align:middle line:84%
Head is always touching,
always off balance.

00:56:24.310 --> 00:56:30.710 align:middle line:90%


00:56:30.710 --> 00:56:33.530 align:middle line:84%
>>How long do I have to wait
for it to be white again?

00:56:33.530 --> 00:56:40.070 align:middle line:90%


00:56:40.070 --> 00:56:45.020 align:middle line:84%
>>Just because you can't see
it doesn't mean it isn't there.

00:56:45.020 --> 00:56:51.360 align:middle line:90%


00:56:51.360 --> 00:56:56.625 align:middle line:84%
The heart is much faster
and wiser than the head.

00:56:56.625 --> 00:57:00.020 align:middle line:84%
In the eyes of the heart,
black and white judgments

00:57:00.020 --> 00:57:06.410 align:middle line:84%
disappear because the heart
is balanced by a deeper truth.

00:57:06.410 --> 00:57:12.370 align:middle line:84%
The great spirit spins together
moments of profound beauty

00:57:12.370 --> 00:57:16.410 align:middle line:84%
that can only be
experienced with the heart.

00:57:16.410 --> 00:57:22.170 align:middle line:90%


00:57:22.170 --> 00:57:25.760 align:middle line:84%
>>I am forever grateful
for that bathroom.

00:57:25.760 --> 00:57:29.960 align:middle line:84%
To see where evil
can take people,

00:57:29.960 --> 00:57:33.460 align:middle line:84%
but to see also where
love can take people.

00:57:33.460 --> 00:57:37.030 align:middle line:84%
Just realize the
weakness of people,

00:57:37.030 --> 00:57:40.550 align:middle line:84%
but the strength that is
within each one of us.

00:57:40.550 --> 00:57:44.240 align:middle line:84%
To push me that far,
to dig within my heart,

00:57:44.240 --> 00:57:46.786 align:middle line:84%
and to trust that
instinct within.

00:57:46.786 --> 00:57:50.000 align:middle line:90%


00:57:50.000 --> 00:57:53.230 align:middle line:84%
>>And when you can
give thanks for it all

00:57:53.230 --> 00:57:59.360 align:middle line:84%
and love without conditions,
then you will be free.

00:57:59.360 --> 00:58:01.529 align:middle line:90%
That is the power of the heart.

00:58:01.529 --> 00:58:06.020 align:middle line:90%


00:58:06.020 --> 00:58:09.170 align:middle line:90%
>>Life is full of challenges.

00:58:09.170 --> 00:58:12.260 align:middle line:84%
Challenges and
hardships often times

00:58:12.260 --> 00:58:16.040 align:middle line:84%
are the intense
heat and fire that

00:58:16.040 --> 00:58:19.100 align:middle line:84%
break us open to
discover gifts, talents,

00:58:19.100 --> 00:58:22.580 align:middle line:84%
and capacities within us that
we would have never discovered

00:58:22.580 --> 00:58:23.870 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:58:23.870 --> 00:58:26.570 align:middle line:84%
>>So like a match
that holds fire,

00:58:26.570 --> 00:58:29.420 align:middle line:84%
but until it strikes against
something you have no flame.

00:58:29.420 --> 00:58:32.270 align:middle line:90%


00:58:32.270 --> 00:58:34.730 align:middle line:84%
By rubbing up
against experience,

00:58:34.730 --> 00:58:40.569 align:middle line:84%
our heart comes aflame, and
light and warmth come from us.

00:58:40.569 --> 00:58:42.110 align:middle line:10%
>>You can even be
grateful for things

00:58:42.110 --> 00:58:45.570 align:middle line:10%
that you imagine that
aren't any good for you.

00:58:45.570 --> 00:58:48.140 align:middle line:10%
That you imagine that you don't
really want, or that you wish

00:58:48.140 --> 00:58:50.270 align:middle line:10%
you hadn't had to experience.

00:58:50.270 --> 00:58:54.980 align:middle line:84%
Even in those moments,
masters say thank you to life,

00:58:54.980 --> 00:58:57.979 align:middle line:84%
thank you to God, thank
you to the divine self

00:58:57.979 --> 00:58:59.270 align:middle line:90%
for this particular experience.

00:58:59.270 --> 00:59:01.490 align:middle line:84%
Because I know that
before too long I

00:59:01.490 --> 00:59:03.920 align:middle line:84%
will see the
extraordinary gift that

00:59:03.920 --> 00:59:09.410 align:middle line:84%
has been folded into
this physical encounter.

00:59:09.410 --> 00:59:13.880 align:middle line:84%
>>Six months after the genocide,
and people used to tell me,

00:59:13.880 --> 00:59:16.140 align:middle line:90%
you can't forgive this quick.

00:59:16.140 --> 00:59:21.220 align:middle line:90%
It's too quick to be happy.

00:59:21.220 --> 00:59:23.330 align:middle line:84%
You can't be smiling
after what happened.

00:59:23.330 --> 00:59:26.132 align:middle line:90%


00:59:26.132 --> 00:59:29.450 align:middle line:84%
And that really kind of made
me question a little bit

00:59:29.450 --> 00:59:30.890 align:middle line:90%
sometimes.

00:59:30.890 --> 00:59:38.990 align:middle line:84%
I said, am I happy and forgiving
out of surviving mechanism?

00:59:38.990 --> 00:59:40.350 align:middle line:90%
Am I going to crush one day?

00:59:40.350 --> 00:59:43.650 align:middle line:84%
Which many people told me,
on one day, if you see them,

00:59:43.650 --> 00:59:45.300 align:middle line:90%
you will go back to the anger.

00:59:45.300 --> 00:59:46.500 align:middle line:90%
I said, really?

00:59:46.500 --> 00:59:47.430 align:middle line:90%
Let me see.

00:59:47.430 --> 00:59:51.990 align:middle line:84%
So I went to prison to see the
person who have killed my mom

00:59:51.990 --> 00:59:55.470 align:middle line:84%
and my brother, whom I would
not have gone to meet him.

00:59:55.470 --> 00:59:57.540 align:middle line:90%
It didn't serve me one bit.

00:59:57.540 --> 01:00:00.960 align:middle line:84%
So I went there just to
really see how I feel.

01:00:00.960 --> 01:00:03.630 align:middle line:84%
And I have learned
the head of the jail

01:00:03.630 --> 01:00:06.480 align:middle line:84%
is a friend of my
father who lost his wife

01:00:06.480 --> 01:00:08.310 align:middle line:90%
and like five children.

01:00:08.310 --> 01:00:11.750 align:middle line:84%
So I knew he would
open the door for me.

01:00:11.750 --> 01:00:14.910 align:middle line:84%
>>You can hit him,
you can do whatever

01:00:14.910 --> 01:00:20.440 align:middle line:90%
you want because I'm here now.

01:00:20.440 --> 01:00:21.370 align:middle line:90%
I will protect you.

01:00:21.370 --> 01:00:24.250 align:middle line:90%


01:00:24.250 --> 01:00:25.710 align:middle line:90%
So ease up your pain.

01:00:25.710 --> 01:00:44.368 align:middle line:90%


01:00:44.368 --> 01:00:45.860 align:middle line:90%
>>And he brought the man.

01:00:45.860 --> 01:00:50.670 align:middle line:90%


01:00:50.670 --> 01:00:51.510 align:middle line:90%
I remember him.

01:00:51.510 --> 01:00:53.950 align:middle line:90%
He used to be a teacher.

01:00:53.950 --> 01:00:56.020 align:middle line:90%
He was like a father to me.

01:00:56.020 --> 01:00:57.520 align:middle line:90%
He had kids my age.

01:00:57.520 --> 01:01:02.090 align:middle line:84%
I used to visit them, and
have lunch with the family.

01:01:02.090 --> 01:01:05.240 align:middle line:90%
Now that's him who did that?

01:01:05.240 --> 01:01:06.980 align:middle line:90%
I just broke down and cried.

01:01:06.980 --> 01:01:10.660 align:middle line:90%


01:01:10.660 --> 01:01:12.380 align:middle line:84%
And I truly cried
out of compassion

01:01:12.380 --> 01:01:14.030 align:middle line:90%
towards him and his family.

01:01:14.030 --> 01:01:42.365 align:middle line:90%


01:01:42.365 --> 01:01:43.850 align:middle line:90%
>>I forgive you.

01:01:43.850 --> 01:01:50.780 align:middle line:90%


01:01:50.780 --> 01:01:52.265 align:middle line:90%
I forgive you.

01:01:52.265 --> 01:01:56.750 align:middle line:90%


01:01:56.750 --> 01:02:00.060 align:middle line:84%
>>It wasn't like, oh, I
planned to say these words.

01:02:00.060 --> 01:02:01.950 align:middle line:84%
There's something I
wanted to express,

01:02:01.950 --> 01:02:05.060 align:middle line:84%
and I couldn't find
words to say it fully.

01:02:05.060 --> 01:02:07.670 align:middle line:90%
I wanted him to be free from me.

01:02:07.670 --> 01:02:10.200 align:middle line:84%
Not to think, oh,
she's mad at me.

01:02:10.200 --> 01:02:11.804 align:middle line:90%
You know, I can't do nothing.

01:02:11.804 --> 01:02:13.220 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted him
to have a chance

01:02:13.220 --> 01:02:16.230 align:middle line:84%
to go through his own
journey from his own heart,

01:02:16.230 --> 01:02:18.530 align:middle line:84%
not because somebody
is angry at him,

01:02:18.530 --> 01:02:20.085 align:middle line:90%
or someone put him in a prison.

01:02:20.085 --> 01:02:21.440 align:middle line:90%
>>What is wrong with you?

01:02:21.440 --> 01:02:28.230 align:middle line:90%


01:02:28.230 --> 01:02:31.370 align:middle line:84%
>>And the head of
the jail was so mad.

01:02:31.370 --> 01:02:33.666 align:middle line:90%
>>What is wrong with you, huh?

01:02:33.666 --> 01:02:37.230 align:middle line:84%
You do not know
what he did to us?

01:02:37.230 --> 01:02:39.750 align:middle line:84%
You do not love
your parents, huh?

01:02:39.750 --> 01:02:42.100 align:middle line:90%
You forget?

01:02:42.100 --> 01:02:44.165 align:middle line:84%
